article.headline: Utah St. 58, Hawaii 50
article.story: LOGAN, Utah (AP) -- Stephen DuCharme scored 15 points and pulled down nine rebounds to pace Utah State University to a 58-50 win over the University of Hawaii Wednesday night. Jaycee Carroll scored 11 and pulled down nine rebounds for the Aggies (19-7, 8-4 Western Athletic Conference). Chris Session added 10 points. The Rainbow Warriors (14-12, 5-8 WAC) were led by Matt Lojeski with 16 points on 7-for-15 shooting. Ahmet Gueye scored 15 with a team-high eight rebounds and Riley Luettgerodt added 11 points. Late in the game, Hawaii scored four points from the free throw line and put back a missed free throw to bring the score to 54-50 with 1:40 to play. Hawaii then missed two field goal attempts and Kris Clark sealed the game for USU when he stole an inbounds pass and scored with 21 seconds remaining in the game. Tight defenses and patient offenses kept both teams from gaining much of an edge in the first half. A fast-break dunk by DuCharme followed by a 3-point shot from Carroll gave USU a 22-16 lead with 3:30 to play, which carried the Aggies to a 27-22 halftime lead. USU committed 15 turnovers in the first half, 25 for the game. Hawaii shot 2-for-18 from the 3-point line.
